<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - MANIFOLDS - EXHAUST MANIFOLD - INSPECTION</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="2">
        <title>INSPECTION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Visually inspect the exhaust manifold for cracks. Replace as required.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect for warpage as follows: (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150305">3.5</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                )
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the exhaust manifold to the cylinder head
                    <emph type="bold">WITHOUT THE GASKET(S)</emph>. Tighten bolts or nuts to specified torque.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Using a .010 in. (0.25 mm) feeler gauge, measure gap between the nuts at the manifold
                    flange to cylinder head mating surface.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If feeler gauge passes through, the exhaust manifold requires resurfacing.</para>
                <figure id="ef4150304" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11530" filename="../figcg1/CG11530.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.4 Exhaust Manifold Removal</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150305" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11531" filename="../figcg1/CG11531.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.5 Checking for Warpage</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>A MAXIMUM OF .025 IN. (0.64 mm) MATERIAL CAN BE GROUND OFF TO CORRECT WARPAGE.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">3. If warpage cannot be corrected by grinding replace the exhaust manifold.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
